  "texts": [
    "In all cases, queries and reference items are aggregated treatment-level profiles matched using the cosine similarity (Methods).",
    "The result of searching the library with one treatment query is a ranked list of treatments in descending order of relevance.",
    "A result in the ranked list is considered a positive hit if it shares at least one biological annotation in common with the query; otherwise it is a negative result (Fig. 1G).",
    "There are several quantitative evaluations of feature representation quality that we use in our study.",
    "At the single-cell level, we expect neural networks to classify single cells into their corresponding treatment, and therefore use accuracy, precision and recall to evaluate performance (see Fig. 3 and main text)."
